  {%- comment -%}FAQ{%- endcomment -%}
  <section class="lp-faq" aria-label="Frequently asked questions">
    <div class="lp-faq__inner">
      <div class="lp-faq__head">
        <p class="lp-faq__eyebrow bbi-mono">Common questions</p>
        <h2>What institutional buyers ask before sending the PO.</h2>
        <p class="lp-faq__cta">Still have a question? <a href="tel:18008359565">Call 1-800-835-9565</a> or <a href="/pages/quote">request a quote</a> and we&rsquo;ll get back to you in 1 business day.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="lp-faq__list">

        <details class="lp-faq-item">
          <summary>
            <span class="lp-faq-item__num">01</span>
            <span class="lp-faq-item__q">Which sectors are eligible to buy under OECM Agreement 2025-470?</span>
            <span class="lp-faq-item__icon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
          </summary>
          <div class="lp-faq-item__body">
            <p>Any OECM-eligible organization: Ontario school boards (K&ndash;12), publicly-assisted colleges and universities, hospitals and CCACs, municipalities and their agencies, broader-public-sector organizations, and not-for-profits in social services and education. If you&rsquo;re not sure, OECM publishes the eligible-buyer list on their site, or call 1-800-835-9565 and we&rsquo;ll confirm in five minutes.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="lp-faq-item">
          <summary>
            <span class="lp-faq-item__num">02</span>
            <span class="lp-faq-item__q">Do I still need internal sign-off if I&rsquo;m OECM-eligible?</span>
            <span class="lp-faq-item__icon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
          </summary>
          <div class="lp-faq-item__body">
            <p>Yes &mdash; your organization&rsquo;s purchasing policy still applies (signing limits, board approvals, internal PO authorization). What disappears under Agreement 2025-470 is the open-tender step. Most OECM buyers go quote &rarr; internal PO authorization &rarr; Brant Business Interiors PO. The 6&ndash;8 weeks normally spent issuing an RFP, evaluating bids, and writing a contract is what you skip.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="lp-faq-item">
          <summary>
            <span class="lp-faq-item__num">03</span>
            <span class="lp-faq-item__q">What&rsquo;s the typical lead time on a multi-room institutional order?</span>
            <span class="lp-faq-item__icon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
          </summary>
          <div class="lp-faq-item__body">
            <p>Most in-stock seating and storage ships within 2&ndash;3 weeks. Custom-configured or upholstered pieces (boardroom tables, COM seating, panel systems) are typically 6&ndash;10 weeks depending on the manufacturer. We confirm lead time per line on every quote and flag anything long-lead clearly. Tell us your move-in or term-start date and we&rsquo;ll work backwards from there.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="lp-faq-item">
          <summary>
            <span class="lp-faq-item__num">04</span>
            <span class="lp-faq-item__q">Do you accept POs, NET-30, and invoiced accounts for private-sector buyers too?</span>
            <span class="lp-faq-item__icon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
          </summary>
          <div class="lp-faq-item__body">
            <p>Yes. Purchase orders, NET-30, and invoiced accounts are standard for both institutional and private-sector buyers &mdash; no credit card required. Credit applications take 1&ndash;2 business days. If your accounts payable needs a specific invoice format, PO reference field, or split billing across departments, we accommodate it on the quote.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="lp-faq-item">
          <summary>
            <span class="lp-faq-item__num">05</span>
            <span class="lp-faq-item__q">Does every quote include a free space plan?</span>
            <span class="lp-faq-item__icon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
          </summary>
          <div class="lp-faq-item__body">
            <p>Yes &mdash; free 2D layout on every project. Send your floor plan (AutoCAD, PDF, or a rough sketch) and our design team sizes the pieces, specs the finishes, and shows you the layout before you commit. For larger fit-outs we provide product callouts and a finish schedule. On-site measure available when needed.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="lp-faq-item">
          <summary>
            <span class="lp-faq-item__num">06</span>
            <span class="lp-faq-item__q">How does delivery and installation work across Ontario?</span>
            <span class="lp-faq-item__icon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
          </summary>
          <div class="lp-faq-item__body">
            <p>Brant Business Interiors&rsquo; own crew handles delivery, assembly, levelling, and removal of old furniture &mdash; we don&rsquo;t subcontract logistics. Delivery is across Canada; installation is Ontario and Western Canada. After-hours and weekend installs are available for occupied spaces (operating clinics, schools in session, municipal buildings during business hours). W5-cleared installers for hospital and ministry sites.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="lp-faq-item">
          <summary>
            <span class="lp-faq-item__num">07</span>
            <span class="lp-faq-item__q">Can you handle multi-site institutional rollouts (e.g., 11 schools, 4 hospital wings)?</span>
            <span class="lp-faq-item__icon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
          </summary>
          <div class="lp-faq-item__body">
            <p>Yes &mdash; multi-site is most of our institutional work. We quote per-site with a master roll-up, sequence installs against your operational calendar (summer for schools, after-hours for clinical sites), and ship to a single warehouse or direct-to-site depending on what your facilities team prefers. One Ontario project manager owns the file across every location.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

